image.altText: Side profile of Guy Barnett and Jeremy Rockliff.

props.synopsis: Tasmanian Treasurer Guy Barnett has handed down his first state budget. What it shows is the smallest state facing big challenges.

title.children: Smallest state has big financial challenges ahead

image.altText: A red and white passenger ferry docked in a bay with the blue sky in the background.

props.synopsis: Both of Tasmania's brand new Bass Strait ferries have "technical issues" with their LNG systems, the government has said — adding to the list of problems which have plagued the ships.

image.altText: Two women holding an indigenous Australian flag that is printed with the word 'WELCOME'.

title.children: This councillor proposed ending Welcomes to Country. The answer was a resounding 'no'.

image.altText: A woman stands on a rock and looks out at a beach.

title.children: Inexperience, drugs, incorrect gear contributed to drowning, coroner finds

image.altText: Visualisation of the exterior of proposed stadium at night.

image.altText: People gathered for NAIDOC Rally. One lady holds a sign that reads 'Treaty'.

title.children: Tasmanian government to drop treaty process and focus on truth-telling

image.altText: A woman with blonde hair in a composite with a woman with brunette hair.

title.children: Lambie successful, Hanson misses out, as Senate results finalised

image.altText: A woman smiles at the camera. In the background are shelves of boxes and a wig hanging from the top.

image.altText: A headshot of James Bailie.

image.altText: A smiling, middle-aged woman with shoulder-length hair cuddles up with a smiling, fair-haired young man.

image.altText: Several people standing in a line and holding a large Russian flag.

image.altText: Woman in foreground and man looking towards her.
